						 <p>My entry for the Pulp Fiction JamCon theme. Written in a few hours while I was at work today. Thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/9volt" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2800867&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1552434241" alt="9Volt" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2800867)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/9volt" >9Volt</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1552434241" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" >GreenWolf</a></span> for critique. Special thanks to 9Volt, whose own Pulp Fiction entry—which I crosslinked to—inspired me to slap the CI into this bad boy. The Spanish word for &quot;fox&quot; is &quot;zorro&quot;, in case that wasn't obvious.</p> 
